title: Mona Lisa
description: The Mona Lisa is a half-length portrait painting by the Italian artist Leonardo da Vinci.

title: The Starry Night
description: The Starry Night is an oil on canvas by Dutch post-impressionist painter Vincent van Gogh.

title: The Storm on the Sea of Galilee
description: The Storm on the Sea of Galilee is a 1633 oil-on-canvas painting by the Dutch Golden Age painter Rembrandt van Rijn.

title: Van Gogh self-portrait
description: Dutch Post-Impressionist artist Vincent van Gogh painted a self-portrait in oil on canvas in September 1889.

title: The Potato Eaters
description: The Potato Eaters is an oil painting by Dutch artist Vincent van Gogh painted in April 1885 in Nuenen, Netherlands.

title: The Abbey in the Oakwood
description: The Abbey in the Oakwood is an oil painting by Caspar David Friedrich. It was painted between 1809 and 1810 in Dresden and was first shown together with the painting The Monk by the Sea in the Prussian Academy of Arts exhibition of 1810.

title: I lock my door upon myself
Wanderer above the Sea of Fog
description: Wanderer above the Sea of Fog, also known as Wanderer above the Mist or Mountaineer in a Misty Landscape, is an oil painting c. 1818 by the German Romantic artist Caspar David Friedrich.

title: The Swing
description: The Swing, also known as The Happy Accidents of the Swing, is an 18th-century oil painting by Jean-Honoré Fragonard in the Wallace Collection in London.
